  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      In General anesthesia, two main ways of pain control are used intra-operatively, one is
      opioids, the other is epidural. Many colleges prefer using epidural analgesia because it is
      potent and more effective , and also the benefits of stress block, less depression of breath.
      however, the epidural technique often causes more drop of blood pressure, especially in
      dehydrated patients. The investigators designed the trial to see if the benefit weigh out the
      potential risk of epidural in isolated hypertensive patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
